Launching Gazebo and rviz
Step 1 — Remove the duplicate (keep only the one directly in src/)
rm -rf ~/ros2_ws/src/aqua_waste_robot
Step 2 — Build now
cd ~/ros2_ws
colcon build --packages-select aqua_robot_gazebo
source install/setup.bash
Step 3 — Launch
export LIBGL_ALWAYS_SOFTWARE=1
export MESA_GL_VERSION_OVERRIDE=3.3
ros2 launch aqua_robot_gazebo multi_robot_safe.launch.py

export LIBGL_ALWAYS_SOFTWARE=1
export MESA_GL_VERSION_OVERRIDE=3.3
ros2 launch aqua_robot_gazebo lake_simulation.launch.py robot_x:=10.0 ro
bot_y:=30.0


Step 5: Verify Robot Exists
In a new terminal:
cd ~/ros2_ws
source install/setup.bash

ros2 topic list
You should see ROS topics from your robot.

opening world sdf file
nano ~/ros2_ws/src/aqua_robot_gazebo/worlds/lake_waste.world
opening robot sdf
nano ~/ros2_ws/src/aqua_robot_gazebo/launch/multi_robot_safe.launch.py
opening robot urdf file
nano ~/ros2_ws/src/aqua_robot_gazebo/urdf/aqua_robot_multi.urdf.xacro


